YENAGOA – The University of Port Harcourt (UNIPORT) Alumni Association has congratulated one of its own and former Chairman of Abua/Odual Local Government Area of Rivers State, Udi Odum, on his nomination by President Muhammadu Buhari as a Federal Minister. Odum was among a list of seven ministerial nominees whose names were contained in a letter Buhari forwarded to the Senate requesting their screening and confirmation. The senate president, Ahmad Lawan, had read the president’s letter on the floor at the start of the plenary on Tuesday. According to the association, the nomination of Odum is a testament that the institution is a breeding ground for generational leaders who have a lot to offer in raising the bar of the country’s socio-economic development. In a congratulatory letter dated June 24, the national president of the UNIPORT alumni, Williams Ule Glad, described Odum as “a thoroughbred leader and a consummate community manager who has for years stood out, not only in discharging leadership assignments but in academic brilliance.” He said the appointment of Odum was also an attestation of his pedigree and remarkable qualities which he had over the years showcased to the world as a good ambassador of his alma mater and a two-time Abua/Odual council area boss. Glad advised the ministerial nominee to see his appointment as a call for service and an opportunity to demonstrate the unique qualities instilled in him by the university and the association. He further said, “I write to congratulate you on your nomination as a Federal Minister by His Excellency, President Muhammadu Buhari GCFR. -Advertisement- POLL “I urge you to see this as a call to service and a great opportunity to put on display the spirit of hard work, service and excellence which the University of Port Harcourt and our association are known for. “On behalf of myself, the entire members of Unique University of Port Harcourt Alumni Association, I congratulate you and wish you success.”